The paper proposes a deep learning framework for unsupervised clustering using collaborative representation restricted Boltzmann machines (CRRBM) and collaborative representation Gaussian restricted Boltzmann machines (CRGRBM). The paper falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a deep learning framework. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses deep learning techniques for unsupervised clustering. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with modeling real-valued data. The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it uses restricted Boltzmann machines. Finally, the paper involves social and information networks (cs.SI) as it uses locality-sensitive hashing to generate similar sample subsets.
